### Goal: Convergent Improvement

The model succeeds when:
- Each new class implementation has **fewer crashes** than the previous one
- The ratio of **predictable errors to total errors** approaches 100%
- **Build iterations per feature** trends toward 1
- **New pattern discoveries** trend toward 0 (the model captures all recurring failure modes)

The model fails when the same error category occurs in consecutive sessions — this means either the pattern wasn't followed (process gap) or the pattern's mitigation is incomplete (knowledge gap). Both are addressable: process gaps by better checklist discipline, knowledge gaps by updating the pattern.

